metadata.name: Lucid Dream #167
metadata.description:
Lucid Dream is our contribution to celebrate #fxhashturnsone!

 It’s our first long-form collection with shaders! Throughout the year we had the opportunity to explore and improve ourselves. Therefore, we wanted to celebrate this anniversary with a technique/medium that is new to us.

You can explore hidden textures and colors by interacting the animation with your cursor.

“Lucid dreaming is the experience of achieving conscious awareness of dreaming while still asleep. Lucid dreams are generally thought to arise from non-lucid dreams in REM sleep (Stephen LaBerge, 1986).“

----Best experienced in full screen----

Probabilities;

- Unique preview features (exclusive for preview image)

- Generative color palette

- 2 different light styles

- 4 different interaction animation styles 

- Some unique features

This piece is using shaders thus results may be different from device to device.

You can press 's' in liveMode to save the current state as .png.

Half of the primary sales go to the Processing Foundation.

Made with p5js and openGL shaders.
@distcollective, November 2022

metadata.name: gnarly tree #13
metadata.description: Hello! I'm a software developer and plant lover. I have always had a fascination for generative algorithms, fractals, and artificial life. This is my first generative NFT - a gnarly old tree. Source code was written in Scala.js with use of Three.js and ZIO. The algorithm is heavily inspired by l-systems (Lindenmayer systems), but has my own unique quirks. Sections of the tree grow and bend over time to create the final result. Being the first version of the algorithm, it is quite rough around the edges, but I hope you will agree that roughness creates a certain unique charm.

metadata.name: ZigZag Garden #99
metadata.description:
A generative garden drawn with zig-zag lines.
8 different color palettes and various different vegetation-densities.

In Live-Mode...
...press 'r' to toggle square/full-screen ratio.
...press 'p' to overlay the basic color-palette
...press ‘1’ - ‘6’ for high-res downloads (the higher the number the higher the resolution)

Open two different tokens of 'ZigZag Garden' with the same browser to mix their colors!

Created with p5.js using post5 and map2.

-@TeNinEightNFTs

metadata.name: a pale reflection #149
metadata.description:
a canvas is prepared; grids and vignette applied.

marks are added (or not)

a drawing method is chosen

the drawing method is iterated, resulting in a heavily stippled image

the image is sent to a shader

various maths occur inside the shader

the resulting shaded image is then given a border

and thus to the screen

a pale reflection - original music here: https://rtsixty.bandcamp.com/track/pale-reflection 
listen while waiting to be signed.

99.9% of royalties to original minter.

metadata.name: Annum #3597
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Geode #4
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - “slow=1”: Draw only one shape per frame.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: fx(splash) #170
metadata.description:
To celebrate fx(hash) turning 1 year old I've created this token as a part of the #fxhashturnsone event! It's a playful and colorful token symbolizing the experiences I've had with this platform.


The piece uses shaders to generate it's visuals which means that outputs will vary from device to device, and the preview might not look the exact same as your live view.

For that same reason I do not recommend running this piece on a mobile device as the shaders can be quite heavy and blurry on lower-tier hardware. My recommended way of viewing this token is on a pc.


--

To open the export menu double click the screen. Here you can export in a multitude of resolutions.

--


50% of primary proceeds will be donated to the processing foundation, learn more about them here:
https://processingfoundation.org

Made with opengl shaders and p5js by WootScoot, 2022.
